                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d783">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00112 European War 1939/83a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Norway</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-09-13T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 13, 1939—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>34. The questions involved in the maintenance and control of Norwegian trade with
                    the belligerents are, of course, of great interest to us and we are anxious to
                    be kept fully and promptly informed in detail of all developments resulting from
                    British or German proposals to Norway in this connection. We believe that if you
                    approach the appropriate Norwegian authorities for detailed information they may
                    probably gladly keep you currently informed. The Norwegian Government can be
                    assured that any information which it may be willing to impart to you will be
                    held by us in the strictest confidence.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
